Baltimore Crime Data Analysis

2020-07-14 数据科学·数据分析 Baltimore·Crime·Data Science

Overview


The United States is a free and democratic county, but its crime rate has been high all the time. Baltimore is one of the highest crime rate cities. So we are trying to analysis the crimes in Baltimore which happened in the passed few years, may be we can find some interesting features.




Loading and Cleaning Data


datadir <- ‘/Users/chuangchuangzhang/Documents/Data/crime’
rootDir <- getwd()
setwd(file.path(datadir))
baltimore <- read.csv(‘Baltimore.csv’, header = TRUE)
setwd(rootDir)

Now we try to get some basic information about this data.


dim(baltimore)

## [1] 306604      7

names(baltimore)

## [1] "CrimeDate"    "CrimeCode"    "Location"     "Description"  "Weapon"
## [6] "District"     "Neighborhood"

str(baltimore)

## ‘data.frame’:    306604 obs. of  7 variables:
##  $ CrimeDate   : chr  "06/27/2020" "06/27/2020" "06/27/2020" "06/27/2020" …
##  $ CrimeCode   : chr  "5D" "4A" "4E" "7A" …
##  $ Location    : chr  "2700 W NORTH AVE" "3800 S HANOVER ST" "900 STOLL ST" "500 SUNSET RD" …
##  $ Description : chr  "BURGLARY" "AGG. ASSAULT" "COMMON ASSAULT" "AUTO THEFT" …
##  $ Weapon      : chr  NA "FIREARM" NA NA …
##  $ District    : chr  "SOUTHWEST" "SOUTHERN" "SOUTHERN" "SOUTHWEST" …
##  $ Neighborhood: chr  "WALBROOK" "BROOKLYN" "BROOKLYN" "" …

baltimore <- baltimore %>%
    filter(!is.na(CrimeDate))

baltimore$CrimeDate <- strptime(baltimore$CrimeDate, ‘%m/%d/%Y’)
baltimore$Year <- year(baltimore$CrimeDate)
baltimore$Month <- month(baltimore$CrimeDate, label = TRUE, abbr = FALSE)
baltimore$MonthDay <- mday(baltimore$CrimeDate)
baltimore$YearDay <- yday(baltimore$CrimeDate)
baltimore$Weekday <- wday(baltimore$CrimeDate, label = TRUE)

baltimore$CrimeGroup[grepl("ROBBERY", baltimore$Description)] <- "ROBBERY"
baltimore$CrimeGroup[grepl("ASSAULT", baltimore$Description)] <- "ASSAULT"
baltimore$CrimeGroup[grepl("LARCENY", baltimore$Description)] <- "LARCENY"
baltimore$CrimeGroup[grepl("ARSON", baltimore$Description)] <- "ARSON"
baltimore$CrimeGroup[grepl("RAPE", baltimore$Description)] <- "RAPE"
baltimore$CrimeGroup[grepl("SHOOTING", baltimore$Description)] <- "SHOOTING"
baltimore$CrimeGroup[grepl("AUTO THEFT", baltimore$Description)] <- "AUTO THEFT"
baltimore$CrimeGroup[grepl("HOMICIDE", baltimore$Description)] <- "HOMICIDE"
baltimore$CrimeGroup[grepl("BURGLARY", baltimore$Description)] <- "BURGLARY"

baltimore$CrimeScore[baltimore$CrimeGroup=="ROBBERY"] <-7
baltimore$CrimeScore[baltimore$CrimeGroup=="AUTO THEFT"] <-6
baltimore$CrimeScore[baltimore$CrimeGroup=="SHOOTING"] <-6
baltimore$CrimeScore[baltimore$CrimeGroup=="ASSAULT"] <-8
baltimore$CrimeScore[baltimore$CrimeGroup=="BURGLARY"] <-6
baltimore$CrimeScore[baltimore$CrimeGroup=="HOMICIDE"] <-10
baltimore$CrimeScore[baltimore$CrimeGroup=="LARCENY"] <-4
baltimore$CrimeScore[baltimore$CrimeGroup=="ARSON"] <-5
baltimore$CrimeScore[baltimore$CrimeGroup=="RAPE"] <-9
baltimore$CrimeScore <- as.factor(baltimore$CrimeScore)

Exploring Data


Firstly, we want to know the change of number of incidents in the passed.



We found that data before 2014 were not accurate, so we only keep the data after 2014.



We can see that 2017 had the highest crime incidents. But it has gradually decreased over over the past three years.


Then how about the crime incidents in different month?



We can find that the February has the lowest crime incidents.


Then what’s the trend in a year?



How about the trrend in a month?



It looks criminal doesn’t select the days they love.


Then what happened in a week?



It looks like Friday has the highest but Sunday has the lowest crime incidents. Criminal may also need to pray in a church.


Next, what kind of weapon they like to use?



Oh, Firearm is their favorite.


What about the regional distribution of crimes?



It looks like Western is a peaceful place, but northeast always on the fire.


Then what about the crime scroe in different district?


## summarise() regrouping output by ‘District’ (override with .groups argument)


Then how changes among crime groups?


## summarise() regrouping output by ‘CrimeGroup’ (override with .groups argument)


It is clear that larceny incidents is the highest in Baltimore.




Summary


By analyzing the crime data about Baltimore. We have found some useful information. Criminal may have their holidays on Feb and they may also need to pray in a church on Sunday. Larceny is the hightest crime incidents in Baltimore, whereas they like to use firearm as weapon.
